        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Mekrath is at level 55, and I am getting a little bit bored of the constant exp grind.  I decided to play an alt a little bit for some variety.  I have tried a bunch of classes in the past and I seem to be drawn to the int casters the most.  Right now I have a 19 Magician, 11 Wizard, and 6 Enchanter.  I'm trying to decide which one to continute to level, as I only have time to play one of them along with my Necromancer.  I would like some words of wisdom from those of you who have tried some of these as alts. Keeping in mind the levels  I have played these 3 to, here is what I have found.</P><P>Magician - at level 19 I feel like a nerfed Necromancer.  I can't fear kite, I can't snare.  I like the pet as I am used to it with my main, but he doesn't seem tough enough to take a beating.  Medding is excruciatingly slow.</P><P>Enchanter - At level 6 I am dying constantly.  It is because I am racing to 8 and taking on stuff I probably shouldn't.  The reason I created the Enchanter is becasue it seems to me that it would be a challenge to play and require thought and strategy.  This character is too young to have seen anything of the class though.  I do NOT intend to jewelcraft, BTW.</P><P>Wizard - At level 11, so far I am having a good time.  Blasting stuff is fun, but I don't know if it will be tedious after a bunch more levels.  I have been able to solo pretty well to this point due to the Lost Staff of the Scorned that my main found in CoM and gave to this character.  It is a 11/24 2HB that is a mana free right click Nek Gate at level 47.  With the damage it does, I can still melee well, though Im sure by 16 that will be over.  I like the fact that I will be able to port, as I hate travel with my necro.  My only concern would be later on nuking and medding might get boring.</P><P>If anyone could relate some experiences that would help me out, I would greatly appreciate it.  Am I missing something about the magician?  Does a Wizard get boring?  Is an Enchanter a great, fun challenge or a PITA?  Thanks!</P><P> </font></td>

