        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I too found being a mage later rather sucky, I think mostly because I thought my mage would get more groups than Saminga. Hell no. I think if you are not a chanter, expect to solo alot.</P><P>Chanters look like a big PITA, OK, I can mez, but I'm not a fan of doing it, it's sort of a "Damn, we have no chanter, mez Sami please." thing. Also, I bet at some point you will tash/mez, get aggro, and try and cast FD or HS and realize, you are not on your necro and go, oh &*^% I am about to die. And then you do.</P><P>Wizard range rocks. And playing a char with decent nukes is really fun. Watch things die real quickly! Seeing how common as dirt (at least on my server) KEIs is, and chanters in general, you too will not be terribly worrying about mana. I would say also, tho, get some HP rings to start, if anything, Wizards get pounded on the most, and I would try and get some AC up also. Chanters get aggro easy, but so do wizards. Also, don't nuke too early, otherwise it will be "Hail, a_nuking_wizard's corpse." And also, remember that you can't use necro tricks to get outta aggro.</P><P>And for the end game, expect not to be grouped unless you a chanter. And on a raid, well, wizards will have more fun, while mages will be making mod rods all day and chanters will dread the /tell Speed plz.</P><P>I personally would stick to your wizard for a sake of variety. As far as INT casters go, it's totally different than a necromancer. No pet, no mezzing or DoTs, just really cool nukes + porting and TLing later.</P><P>Saminga Amaranth, 59th (STILL, yeah, I know :P) Bad Girl of Avatars of Discord, Rodcet Nife.</P><P>Good girls go to Heaven, bad girls FD and /q out.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
