         I've got a magician myself and lately haven't seen any point in leveling the character.  Magicians are such a crap class compared to necros hehe.  And that's not an exaggeration.  When you look at it seriously they only get pets, nukes, invis and gate.  I don't even count their crappy summons.  For necros the pet is just another tool with which to get the job done.  There's just no comparison between the two classes.</P><P>Wizards eh well been there done that.  You're in worse shape than a magician from 1-20.  After 29 things get better and if you have alot of money in the bank you'll have no problem leveling.  Just remember that any class can level fast if you have the cash to dole out for buffs.  Plus since now you can bind in Timor I would say their gating ability is vastly overrated unless you regularly hunt deep into Luclin.  I wouldn't bother with the wizard unless you think the game starts at 60 and are in a hardcore raiding guild.</P><P>I keep meaning to get going on an enchanter but I've played one to 13 and it was a bitch.  Sure 1-10 is real fast and I have a 10/22 1hb in the bank but 12-16 would still be rough for grouping.  Also most people hunt in boring outdoor zones which means all they really want is speed and crack for 49 levels.  Still it's gotta be fun.  I guess my only real problem would be the high level of concentration it takes to play an enchanter well in dungones.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
