         I have a wiz twink I've been gradually working up.  She's 22 now and pretty poorly equipped to be honest, but nonetheless I find that I really enjoy playing her.  I put her on my second account so I'd have a taxi when she got high enough level, and I might even try grouping her when she catches up enough.  (I know there are other classes that are better for this, I already 2 box with a cleric and druid occasionally.)</P><P>Tried a mage for 13 levels, just can't get into it.  Everyone talks about how mages ARE their pets so I figured they would be a lot tougher than they turned out to be.  I guess I just can't get past wanting to play like a necro when you give me a pet.  I actually found the parlor trick summoning stuff to be kinda fun though.</P><P>I have now started and played an enchanter 5 times now, different race each time.  The furthest I got with any of them was level 9.  I think it's a fun class to play, but like a cleric they have such pathetic DPS that I found soloing to be very slow going.  I did not enjoy grouping in outdoor zones where I was mostly just a buff whore, as I started a chanter because I wanted to do CC and rarely found myself doing any (not that it is needed much anyway at the low levels these days with twinks being what they are. )</P><P>If it's gotta be an Int caster, I would suggest a wizard.  I would seriously recommend going to a Wis caster, and pick either a shaman or a dr00d.  Either will solo well and group well, and there are great benefits to either if you have now or ever expect to do any 2 boxing.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22254" target="_blank">Sssyx Syxyx</a><BR><a href="http://eqmoonies.freeservers.com">Spirit of the Moon</a></P><P><a href="mailto:sssyx@mmdog.com">sssyx@mmdog.com</a></P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
