		<a name="40683"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/16/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 03:58:27</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=3874"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3874')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=40683&amp;TOPIC_ID=5017&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Int+caster+alt+for+a+55+Necro&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I'm currently lvling a chanter as my alt (lvl 46).  Quite frankly, its really not what i envisioned.  Dont get me wrong, there are moments where this class totally owns, but those moments seem too few and far in between.  There are very few things that are more exciting and thrilling than locking down a train of 7 mobs, but honestly, its rare that you'll see a pull of over 3 mobs at any point in time.</P><P>Whether we like it or not, the primary structure of an xp group is to have mobs single chain pulled.  Groups tend to congregate in safe xp zones (aka velks, dl, ot, etc...), and heavily shy away from anything that might represent a challenge.  In the absence of a challenging camp (constant multi pulls, roamers, adds, trains), a chanter is pretty much left with 2 functions, buffing (clarity, haste) and debuffing (slowing and tash).  This i have found to be very boring.</P><P>With my chanter, i've boycotted DL, and have avoided the kunark express as much as possible.  The only problem is that the zone's that are ideal for my level (the hole, l guk, etc...), are overcamped by lvl 55+ loot farmers, and are completely void of anyone hunting for xp.  </P><P>A big plus for the class is that its a great group class and finding groups will rarely be an issue.  Its like nite and day in comparison to the necro class, as you'll generally find yourself getting tells when zoning into xp zones appropriate for your lvl.</P><P>So, my advice to you is the following:<BR>- If you lvl your enchanter, have some friends that will level with you.  This is so u can quickly build a group for some of the funner chanter zones and dungeons, and avoid the kunark express like the plague.</P><P>- Be prepared to buff, buff, buff and buff.  Requests for haste and clarity will cycle as the buffs fade.  It sometimes get to the point where terms like crack plz or need speed will make u cringe, because you'll have heard them 100+ in a nite.</P><P>- Be prepared for frustration.  People break mezzes over and over and over again.  Some people cant comprehend the concept of a mez and why its beneficial fora  group to assist the assigned MT.</P><P>- Be prepared to miss your necro.  Chanters cant solo nearly as well as a necro.  Chanters are a relatively impotent offensive class (with the exception of charm). Chanters cant lifetap.  Chanters cant lich. Etc...</P><P>Lastly, no class is as complex or as challenging as a necro.  There are just so many things we can do.  As a chanter, my biggest decisions are whether to AoE mez, or PBAoE stun + single mez a big train.  Everything else is pretty much clockwork.  I miss the complexity of our class and the constant role changes we have as we insert or delete different people from our groups.</P><P>Anyhow, thats my long winded 2cp for u regarding the chanter class. Hope this helps and best of luck finding a good alt.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55675" target="_blank">Tencor Laureate - 60th Warlock</a><br><BR><a href="http://www.veilofsilence.org" target="_blank">Veil of Silence</a><br> <BR>Innoruuk Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

